     </div>
     <p class="about-page__text">Mahila Chetna Samiti (MCS), founded in 1997, is a family bound by hope and heart—a community built by and for women who dream of a brighter tomorrow but face challenges that so often go unheard. As a non-profit registered under the Uttar Pradesh Societies Registration Act, our purpose is deeply rooted in the struggles and aspirations we witness every day in India’s villages. Imagine a woman in a remote village, her hands rough from tireless work, yet her dreams for her daughter’s education shine softly in her eyes. She faces the weight of tradition, limited resources, and the silent pain of being unheard or overlooked. For many women like her, accessing education, healthcare, or even finding a voice in family decisions can feel impossible. </p>
     <p class="about-page__text">At MCS, we walk beside these women, listening to stories about sending a little girl to school for the first time, overcoming fear to speak up at a health camp, or learning something as vital as basic hygiene. Their journey is our inspiration. Through every small victory—one more girl in school, one more woman leading a meeting, one more family embracing awareness—we remember why we began this mission. We believe every woman’s struggle deserves empathy, every hope deserves encouragement, and no dream should be lost to silence. When you join hands with Mahila Chetna Samiti, you become part of a family that refuses to let rural women and children be forgotten, helping transform their pain into purpose and their dreams into reality.</p>
